<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="58476" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Lin, Y. J." journalOrPublisher="China Forestry Publishing House, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476" refId="B6091578" refString="Lin, Y. J., Zhang, S. M., 1993. Animals of Longqi Mountain. China Forestry Publishing House, Beijing" title="Animals of Longqi Mountain" year="1993">Lin and Zhang (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachymna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" lsidName="Brachymna tenuis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">Brachymna tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. castanea" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="castanea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">B. castanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from the latter by the yellowish-brown body colour (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6092365" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">1</figureCitation>
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6092370" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6092371" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">b</figureCitation>
) (ferruginous in 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. castanea" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="castanea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">B. castanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the pygophore bearing dentate postero-lateral processes that are obtusely curved from the postero-ventral margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6092365" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">1</figureCitation>
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6092372" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">c</figureCitation>
) (postero-lateral processes make approximately a right angle with the postero-ventral margin in 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. castanea" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="castanea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="58476">B. castanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
